[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hertfordshire PC Leigh Brightman denies child rape and 10 further charges

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A police officer from Hertfordshire pleaded not guilty to rape and 10 other offences when he appeared in court.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
PC Leigh Brightman, from Hitchin, appeared at the Old Bailey for a plea and case management hearing.
The officer, 36, denied all charges, including one count of rape of a girl aged between 13 and 15 and four of misconduct in a public office.
He is also charged with making four and possessing two indecent photographs of a child.
His trial at the Old Bailey is scheduled to start on 20 July.
PC Brightman is currently suspended from the Hertfordshire force pending the outcome of the trial.
